<title>Engine::Entities</title>
        <section>
            <title> Data Structures </title>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>struct <link linkend="d0/d39/a00314">Engine::Entities::Entity</link></para>
<para><emphasis>&lt;summary&gt;
ABSTRACT CLASS: The Base entity class. All entities extend this class. It contains the basic setup and properties
of each entity.
&lt;/summary&gt;</emphasis></para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>struct <link linkend="d2/d41/a00318">Engine::Entities::Mind</link></para>
<para><emphasis>&lt;summary&gt;
ABSTRACT CLASS: Mind controls the behaviour for a specific entity. The entity is simply the sprite that is drawn
whilst Mind controls how it acts.
&lt;/summary&gt;</emphasis></para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>struct <link linkend="de/de9/a00322">Engine::Entities::pEntity</link></para>
<para><emphasis>&lt;summary&gt;
CLASS: The player Entity class
&lt;/summary&gt;</emphasis></para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
            <para>
                <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>struct <link linkend="d8/d23/a00326">Engine::Entities::PlayerMind</link></para>
<para><emphasis>&lt;summary&gt;
CLASS: The mind that controls the player Entity.
&lt;/summary&gt;</emphasis></para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
            </para>
